def West_Bengal():
    s=pyttsx3.init()
    s.say("West Bengal, the state in eastern India is endowed with uniqueness in its diversity. It offers its visitors a matchless geographical variety. The state is a tourist's paradise which includes hill stations, religious centres, wild life sanctuaries, and sea beaches. West Bengal is a land of magnificent landscape, flora fauna amidst the undulating terrains of the north as well as the effervescent seas in the south. This state is an exceptional amalgamation of culture, entertainment, artistry and boundless life. The streaming populace of the streets offers a strange beauty of the urban milieu, whereas the remote hill stations and sea beaches are perfect retreat for that very hectic urban population. West Bengal has everything of its own to offer through its impeccable natural beauty. ")
    s.say("A dream destination for vacationers, West Bengal is endowed some wonderful hill stations and beaches. The most well-known of all hill stations is Darjeeling. Tourists from all across the world come here to witness the breathtaking views of sun rise on Eastern Himalayas. The toy train ride in Darjeeling contributes to the perfect choice for leisure tourism for the visitors. This magnificent hill resort is a heavenly retreat, bathed in hues of every shade. The burning red rhododendrons, the dazzling white magnolias, the interesting forests of silver fir, the miles of surging hillsides covered with emerald green tea bushes make Darjeeling the 'Queen of Hill Stations'. Darjeeling summons thousands of tourists for a leisurely relief from the hustle and bustle of the madding crowd. The traveler, whether a tourist or a trekker, an ornithologist or a photographer, a botanist or an artist will discover in Darjeeling an experience which will stay etched in ones memory eternally. Kalimpong is another famous hill station of West Bengal. Hidden under the shadows of Eastern Himalayas, the white snow covered hill stations of West Bengal are the main stay of tourism in the state. Mirik and Sandakphu are among the other popular hill stations of West Bengal. The exquisite beaches in West Bengal are a major crowd puller. The Southern West Bengal is gifted with the most well-known beach on the eastern coast of India, which is Digha. This beach town is crowded almost all throughout the year by local visitors as well as tourists from outside the state. Shankarpur, a virgin beach is a recent discovery. It is a twin beach of Digha. It is now developed as a sea resort with hotels, tourist lodges and other facilities. Bakkhali is a popular sea resort of West Bengal. The quiet and charming environment of this place attracts thousands of tourists every year. West Bengal is also noted for some magnificent historical monuments. The district of Murshidabad is a legendary spot in West Bengal which attracts many tourists. The Hazarduari palace of Murshidabad is a famous historical monument and a much visited site for the tourists. It lies amidst extensive gardens and is a fairly flawless example of Italian-style architecture. Plassey is a place of great historical importance. This historic battlefield is still preserved and is visited by many enthusiastic tourists. In the north of West Bengal, the town of Coochbehar is a store house of numerous historical monuments and buildings. The most important landmark of this very old princely state that stands majestically is the splendid Raj Bari or the palace of the kings. The Firoze Minar of Malda in West Bengal is a small imitation of the Qutub Minar in Delhi and is an interesting place to visit. Thus West Bengal has the widest variety of attractions in terms of tourist spots.")
    s.say("West Bengal is a shopper's destination. The state is well-known for the beautiful items of clay, shoal and conch. The Baluchari saris or Bengali silk saris are the main shopping item for the travelers. It is an eminent for its exquisite design and wonderful weaving techniques. These saris are mainly produced at Baluchar town of Murshidabad district of West Bengal. Another major handicraft item of West Bengal is Batik. It involves a Japanese style of work, which comprise wax painting. The delicate look of the fabric is bound to mesmerise the shoppers. The most popular embroidery type of West Bengal is the Kantha stitch which is usually done with folk motifs. Other varieties of embroidery include Chikan work, zari work and the kashida. The cane mats are exclusive items of West Bengal. The design of these mats consists of sequence of motifs of animals, and human and are a must buy for the shoppers. The Darjeeling tea is a hot favourite among the tourists who make it a point to buy some before leaving the state. The vest time to visit West Bengal is during the months of September-October and December-January. The state of West Bengal is finely equipped with an abundance of hotels which offers best of accommodation facilities and services ")
